Building phylogenetic trees with DADA2 ASVs

Since DADA2 is a reference-free approach, a tree needs to be created de novo. Below is the code for creating a phylogenetic tree using the methods outlined in the workflow manuscript Bioconductor Workflow for Microbiome Data Analysis: from raw reads to community analyses by Callahan BJ, Sankaran K, Fukuyama JA, McMurdie PJ, Holmes S. F1000Research 2016, 5:1492, version 2 (https_r50://doi.org/10.12688/f1000research.8986.2)

set.seed(100)
library(phyloseq)
library(DECIPHER)
library(phangorn)
library(ggplot2)
library(here)
library(lubridate)
options(dplyr.summarise.inform = FALSE)

Load the workspace

DADA2_workspace <- "Loop_rarefied_ps_filtered.RData"

# Load RData file
load(here::here("2024_code", DADA2_workspace))

Align sequences with Decipher

# get ASV sequences
seqs<- taxa_names(ps_r50)
names(seqs) <- seqs

start_time <- paste(Sys.Date(), hour(Sys.time()), minute(Sys.time()), sep='-')
message(paste0("begin alignment ", start_time))

# Create alignment with decipher - took 15 - 30 minutes
alignment <- AlignSeqs(DNAStringSet(seqs), anchor=NA)

Build tree with phangorn

start_time <- paste(Sys.Date(), hour(Sys.time()), minute(Sys.time()), sep='-')
message(paste0("begin alignment ", start_time))
## begin alignment 2025-02-28-12-34
## the chunk below up to detaching phangorn below ~20 hours
# Build tree with phangorn
phang.align <- phyDat(as(alignment, "matrix"), type="DNA")
dm <- dist.ml(phang.align)
treeNJ <- NJ(dm) # Note, tip order != sequence order
fit = pml(treeNJ, data=phang.align)

## negative edges length changed to 0! <- warning ok

fitGTR <- update(fit, k=4, inv=0.2)
fitGTR <- optim.pml(fitGTR, model="GTR", optInv=TRUE, optGamma=TRUE,
                      rearrangement = "stochastic", control = pml.control(trace = 0))

end_time <- paste(Sys.Date(), hour(Sys.time()), minute(Sys.time()), sep='-')

difftime(ymd_hm(end_time), ymd_hm(start_time), units = "mins") 
## Time difference of 13 mins
save.image(here::here("Loop_rarefied_ps_phangorn.RData"))

detach("package:phangorn", unload=TRUE)

Add tree to phyloseq object

We use merge_phyloseq to add the phylogenetic tree to the existing phyloseq objects. Warning ASVs may be dropped at this point, so it is important to check if any are dropped. If they are dropped, further investigation must occur to ensure that the dropped ASVs will not have a huge impact on downstream analyses.

# attach to current phyloseq object
ps_r50_tree = merge_phyloseq(ps_r50, phy_tree(fitGTR$tree))
# evaluate
